description.narrative: Community engagement remained an important component of the CSD program. The focus was on the implementation of the roadmap "Free Senegal from open defecation by 2030" expanded to nutrition, health, immunization, menstrual hygiene management and WASH/PCI against Covid 19. Communities are particularly engaged in responses to the various threats recorded in 2021 (Covid-19, polio, measles, Hemorrhagic Virus Fevers, floods, etc.), as well as in promising community strategies such as improved cereal stores. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:02/02/2022
